Template: atlas-voice/welcome
Type: note
Description: Atlas Voice Installation
 Atlas Voice has been installed successfully.
 .
 REQUIREMENTS:
 The following will be downloaded automatically during installation:
 - Whisper large-v3 speech model (~3GB) from huggingface.co/Systran
 .
 All other dependencies (OpenWakeWord, faster-whisper, CUDA runtime
 libraries, etc.) are bundled in the package and run inside an
 isolated Python virtual environment for safety and package isolation.
 .
 STARTING THE SERVICE:
 Atlas Voice runs as a systemd user service. It will be enabled and
 started automatically after installation. To manage it manually:
 .
   systemctl --user start atlas-voice
   systemctl --user stop atlas-voice
   systemctl --user restart atlas-voice
   systemctl --user status atlas-voice
 .
 The service starts automatically with your desktop session on login.
 .
 USAGE:
 Say "Hey Atlas" to activate voice dictation. Speak your text,
 then say "break" to finish and transcribe. The transcribed text
 will be typed into your focused application.
 .
 CONTROLS:
 Click the tray icon to access the menu:
 - Pause / Resume: Toggle wake word listening on or off
 - Enable / Disable (GPU): Load or unload models to free VRAM
 - Quit Atlas: Stop the service
